==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remittent
<hw>Re*mit"tent</hw> <pr>(r?-m?t"t<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>remittens</ets>, p. pr. : cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧mittent</ets>.]</ety> <def>Remitting; characterized by
remission; having remissions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Remittent fever</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a fever
in which the symptoms temporarily abate at regular intervals, but do not
wholly cease. See <altname>Malarial fever</altname>, under
<er>Malarial</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remitter</ent>⟦br⟧
